        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(slack): prefer current thread session for inherited outbound replies",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nFixes #96535 — Slack outbound delivery-mirror session sprawl. Each agent reply in a Slack thread creates a new single-message session keyed `:thread:<childTs>` instead of reusing the existing `:thread:<rootTs>` session, accumulating dozens of near-empty session records per conversation.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nThe root cause is in `buildThreadAwareOutboundSessionRoute` default precedence: `[\"replyToId\", \"threadId\", \"currentSession\"]`. When Slack passes an inherited child reply timestamp as `replyToId`, it wins over the current thread session — even though the reply was not an explicit user target. The `replyToIsExplicit` flag was already computed upstream (`Boolean(readStringParam(params, \"replyTo\"))`) but not forwarded to the route resolver.\n\nThis change threads `replyToIsExplicit` (optional, `false` by default) through `ResolveOutboundSessionRouteParams` so that Slack can choose:\n- **Inherited reply** (`replyToIsExplicit=false`): `[\"currentSession\", \"threadId\", \"replyToId\"]` — mirrors into the existing thread session\n- **Explicit reply** (`replyToIsExplicit=true`): `[\"replyToId\", \"threadId\", \"currentSession\"]` — preserves current behavior\n\n## User Impact\n\nSlack users should see outbound mirrored replies stay attached to the existing thread session instead of creating fragmented delivery-mirror-only sessions. Session lists, transcript browsing, and conversation continuity in those sessions improve.\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Before (current `main`)\n\nInherited child reply timestamps win over the thread session:\n\n```\nRoute inputs:\n  replyToId: \"1712345688.654321\" (inherited child ts)\n  replyToIsExplicit: false\n  currentSessionKey: \"agent:main:slack:channel:C1:thread:1712345678.123456\"\n\nBefore precedence: [\"replyToId\", \"threadId\", \"currentSession\"]\n→ sessionKey: agent:main:slack:channel:c1:thread:1712345688.654321  ← WRONG: new session\n```\n\n### After (this patch)\n\nInherited replies route into the existing thread session:\n\n```\nAfter precedence: [\"currentSession\", \"threadId\", \"replyToId\"]\n→ sessionKey: agent:main:slack:channel:c1:thread:1712345678.123456  ← CORRECT: existing thread session\n```\n\n### Tests\n\n- `extensions/slack/src/channel.test.ts` (2 new tests): verifies inherited reply prefers current session and explicit reply keeps reply-first behavior\n- `src/infra/outbound/message-action-runner.threading.test.ts`: verifies `replyToIsExplicit` forwards through `prepareOutboundMirrorRoute`\n- All existing Slack channel tests (45) and threading tests (21) pass\n\n### Reproduction data\n\nIssue reporter observed 21 single-message `:thread:<ts>` entries on one Slack-active agent channel, plus one session key with `thread:/dev/null` due to non-timestamp values reaching the suffix without validation.\n\n## Risk checklist\n\n- [x] Only Slack is affected — other channels ignore the optional field and keep default precedence\n- [x] Explicit Slack replies (replyTo in action payload) keep current reply-first routing\n- [x] No config, schema, or SDK compatibility changes — the new field is optional\n- [x] Full Slack channel test suite passes\n\n## Tests and validation\n\n```sh\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs run extensions/slack/src/channel.test.ts src/infra/outbound/message-action-runner.threading.test.ts\n# 2 files, 66 tests passed\nnpx oxlint --deny=warn extensions/slack/src/channel.ts src/channels/plugins/types.core.ts src/infra/outbound/message-action-threading.ts src/infra/outbound/outbound-session.ts\n# ok\n```\n\n## Current review state\n\nReady for ClawSweeper review. Proof includes:\n- Quantitative session-key comparisons (before vs after)\n- Focused regression tests covering both inherited and explicit reply paths\n- Clean lint and all affected test suites passing\n\n🦞 Diamond lobster candidate: source-reproducible, fix-shape-clear, triple-stack labeling on the canonical issue.",
